whoWeAre.body:
The data controller within the meaning of Regulation (EU) 2016/679 (GDPR) is {controllerName}.

Stay.hr is a platform for online accommodation bookings and reservation management. Hospira is a reception tablet app that lets staff check guests in, view calendars, and manage reservations.

Contact: {email}
Web: {websiteUrl}
Address: {address}
Tax ID (OIB): {oib}

dataWeCollect.body:
Depending on how you use our services, we may process:

• booker and guest data: name, email, phone, address, stay dates, number of guests;
• check-in and legal registration data: identity document, date of birth, nationality, personal ID number, MRZ data;
• accommodation staff data: username, email, role, language preferences;
• technical data: IP address, access logs, device identifier (FCM token for Hospira tablet), browser information.

We do not request data beyond what is needed for booking, stay, or reception operations.

purposes.body:
We process data to:

• enter into and perform accommodation contracts (online booking, confirmation, guest communication);
• comply with legal obligations (e.g. guest registration via the eVisitor system);
• pursue legitimate interests (system security, abuse prevention, technical support, reasonable archiving);
• rely on consent where required (e.g. optional communication beyond what is necessary).

Without necessary data we cannot provide booking, check-in, or reception services.

recipients.body:
We share data only when necessary with:

• hosting and infrastructure providers (Hetzner);
• Cloudflare (CDN, TLS, protection);
• integrations used by the property: Channex, WhatsApp (Meta), eVisitor, Firebase (push notifications for Hospira);
• competent authorities when required by law.

We use data processing agreements or compliant services with recipients where applicable.

guestBooking.body:
By submitting a request or booking via Stay.hr booking sites:

• you confirm the accuracy of the data you provide;
• you enter into an accommodation contract with the relevant property, not directly with {controllerName} as the accommodation provider;
• you accept that the property confirms availability and stay conditions;
• you accept prices, cancellation rules, and house rules published on the booking site or in the confirmation.

{controllerName} provides the technical platform; stay conditions, on-site payment, and accommodation-related complaints are handled by the property unless stated otherwise in the confirmation.

providers.body:
Accommodation properties and their authorised staff are responsible for:

• accuracy of property data, prices, and availability;
• lawful guest check-in and stay registration;
• security of Hospira tablet and reception web credentials;

Platform access is granted under agreement with {controllerName}. Misuse may result in account suspension.

acceptableUse.body:
You must not:

• submit fake bookings or abuse the booking system;
• access other properties' or users' data without authorisation;
• disrupt platform operation or perform unauthorised automated scraping;
• use the services unlawfully or in violation of third-party rights.

We may restrict access to protect the system and users.

liability.body:
To the extent permitted by law, {controllerName} is not liable for:

• quality of accommodation, property services, or disputes between guests and properties;
• indirect damages, loss of profit, or data loss caused by service interruption;
• content and accuracy of data entered by properties or guests.

Nothing in these terms excludes liability that cannot be excluded under applicable law.
